## 15) Practical end-to-end chronology (single audit run)

1. User uploads PDF in frontend.
2. Ingestion stores file, parses sections, persists document + sections.
3. Frontend displays sections and triggers `POST /audits`.
4. Orchestration starts audit, stamps run metadata.
5. Global scope/mode/posture/obligation precomputation executes.
6. For each section:
   - applicability filtering,
   - issue spotting,
   - legal qualification,
   - retrieval/rerank,
   - evidence sufficiency gate,
   - optional LLM classify,
   - deterministic validation/override,
   - finding + citation persist.
7. Post-loop synthesis/completeness/disposition map execute.
8. Final publication validator and review/publish invariants run.
9. Evidence records + analysis snapshots materialize.
10. Audit enters terminal state.
11. `/findings` provides published projection (unless review-required gate).
12. `/review` and `/review/grouped` provide reviewer triage surfaces.
13. Report endpoint generates PDF from canonical publishable dataset.

